’گگعTitle: title: is-terminal
Path: Examples
Content:
Return "terminal attached" if standard input is attached to a terminal, and "no terminal" if not.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> if (is-terminal --stdin) { "terminal attached" } else { "no terminal" }
terminal attached

```
